{"article_id":"L0E7kOlTfa2FPLbp","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"WASHINGTON -","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"A divided Supreme Court further advanced the cause of LGBTQ rights Monday ,","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"ruling","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"that a landmark civil rights law","depth":9},{"id":4,"text":"barring sex discrimination in the workplace","depth":9},{"id":5,"text":"applies to gay , lesbian and transgender workers .","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"The decision was written by Associate Justice Neil Gorsuch , President Donald Trump 's first nominee to the court .","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"He was joined by Chief Justice John Roberts and the court 's four liberal justices .","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"Associate Justices Samuel Alito , Clarence Thomas and Brett Kavanaugh dissented .","depth":6},{"id":9,"text":"`` An employer","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"who fires an individual","depth":10},{"id":11,"text":"for being homosexual or transgender","depth":10},{"id":12,"text":"fires that person for traits or actions","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"it would not have questioned in members of a different sex , ''","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"Gorsuch wrote .","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"`` Congress adopted broad language","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"making it illegal for an employer to rely on an employee ' s sex","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"when deciding to fire that employee .","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"We do not hesitate to recognize today a necessary consequence of that legislative choice :","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"An employer","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"who fires an individual","depth":11},{"id":21,"text":"merely for being gay or transgender","depth":11},{"id":22,"text":"defies the law . ''","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"Trump ,","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"whose administration took the employers ' side in the case ,","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"suggested","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"the decision was surprising .","depth":7},{"id":27,"text":"But he said :","depth":7},{"id":28,"text":"`` They 've ruled ,","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"and we live with their decision , ''","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"adding","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"it was a `` very powerful decision , actually . ''","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"The court 's ruling is likely to have a sweeping impact on federal civil rights laws","depth":7},{"id":33,"text":"barring sex discrimination in education , health care , housing and financial credit .","depth":7},{"id":34,"text":"Lawsuits","depth":9},{"id":35,"text":"pertaining to those laws","depth":9},{"id":36,"text":"are pending in lower courts ,","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"which are required","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"to follow Supreme Court precedent .","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"The Trump administration 's brand new rule","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"narrowing the legal definition of sex discrimination in health care","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"to omit transgender people","depth":10},{"id":42,"text":"could be jeopardized .","depth":8},{"id":43,"text":"The ruling does not help","depth":7},{"id":44,"text":"when it comes to discrimination against LGBTQ people in public accommodations ,","depth":8},{"id":45,"text":"where discrimination","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"based on sex","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"is not barred by federal law .","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"Thirty-one states do not prohibit discrimination in public accommodations on the basis of sexual orientation or gender identity .","depth":6},{"id":49,"text":"The dramatic ruling came in three cases ,","depth":8},{"id":50,"text":"involving two gay men and a transgender woman , from Georgia , New York and Michigan .","depth":8},{"id":51,"text":"The cases ,","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"heard in early October ,","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"were among the most significant on the court 's docket","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"and had been pending the longest .","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"The challenges from the fired workers picked up","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"where the same-sex marriage battle left off in 2015 ,","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"when the court ruled 5-4","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"that states can not bar gay men or lesbians from matrimony .","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"What was different this time was the court itself :","depth":8},{"id":60,"text":"Gorsuch replaced the late Associate Justice Antonin Scalia ,","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"and Kavanaugh replaced the author of four major opinions","depth":11},{"id":62,"text":"expanding gay rights ,","depth":11},{"id":63,"text":"retired Associate Justice Anthony Kennedy .","depth":10},{"id":64,"text":"The three plaintiffs were Gerald Bostock , a former child welfare services coordinator from Georgia ; Donald Zarda , a former New York skydiving instructor","depth":7},{"id":65,"text":"who died at 44 in 2014","depth":8},{"id":66,"text":"but was represented by his sister and former partner ;","depth":8},{"id":67,"text":"and Aimee Stephens , a former funeral home worker from Michigan","depth":7},{"id":68,"text":"who is transgender ,","depth":8},{"id":69,"text":"and who died March 12 .","depth":8},{"id":70,"text":"Earlier :","depth":6},{"id":71,"text":"Gay rights battle against employment discrimination extends beyond the grave , and to the Supreme Court","depth":7},{"id":72,"text":"At issue :","depth":8},{"id":73,"text":"the text of a 1964 civil rights law","depth":10},{"id":74,"text":"barring employment discrimination","depth":11},{"id":75,"text":"based on sex","depth":11},{"id":76,"text":"and whether that term should be understood to include sexual orientation and gender identity .","depth":9},{"id":77,"text":"Lawyers for the two gay workers said","depth":8},{"id":78,"text":"they were fired","depth":9},{"id":79,"text":"for dating men ,","depth":9},{"id":80,"text":"while female employees were not .","depth":7},{"id":81,"text":"Lawyers for their employers said","depth":7},{"id":82,"text":"they were treated the same","depth":8},{"id":83,"text":"as if they were female employees","depth":9},{"id":84,"text":"who dated women .","depth":9},{"id":85,"text":"Twenty-eight states have little or no workplace protections for the LGBT community .","depth":5},{"id":86,"text":"About 4.5 % of the U.S. population , or roughly 11 million people , identify as lesbian , gay , bisexual , transgender or queer ;","depth":6},{"id":87,"text":"88 % of them are employed .","depth":6},{"id":88,"text":"Former Vice President Joe Biden , the presumptive Democratic nominee","depth":7},{"id":89,"text":"expected to face Trump in November at the polls ,","depth":7},{"id":90,"text":"heralded the court 's decision .","depth":6},{"id":91,"text":"`` The Supreme Court has confirmed the simple but profoundly American idea","depth":10},{"id":92,"text":"that every human being should be treated with respect and dignity","depth":11},{"id":93,"text":"- that everyone should be able to live openly , proudly , as their true selves","depth":12},{"id":94,"text":"without fear , ''","depth":12},{"id":95,"text":"he said in a statement","depth":10},{"id":96,"text":"released shortly after the ruling was announced .","depth":10},{"id":97,"text":"`` This decision is another step in our march towards equality for all . ''","depth":8},{"id":98,"text":"James Esseks of the American Civil Liberties Union ,","depth":10},{"id":99,"text":"which represented Zarda and Stephens ,","depth":10},{"id":100,"text":"said ,","depth":9},{"id":101,"text":"`` The court has caught up to the majority of our country ,","depth":9},{"id":102,"text":"which already knows","depth":10},{"id":103,"text":"that discriminating against LGBTQ people is both unfair and against the law . ''","depth":10},{"id":104,"text":"Alito ,","depth":10},{"id":105,"text":"who wrote more than 100 pages in dissent for himself and Thomas ,","depth":10},{"id":106,"text":"accused the court 's majority of writing legislation ,","depth":10},{"id":107,"text":"not ruling on cases .","depth":10},{"id":108,"text":"`` The question in these cases is not whether discrimination","depth":12},{"id":109,"text":"because of sexual orientation or gender identity","depth":12},{"id":110,"text":"should be outlawed , ''","depth":11},{"id":111,"text":"Alito said .","depth":10},{"id":112,"text":"`` The question is whether Congress did that in 1964 .","depth":10},{"id":113,"text":"It indisputably did not . ''","depth":10},{"id":114,"text":"Writing separately ,","depth":10},{"id":115,"text":"Kavanaugh said simply ,","depth":10},{"id":116,"text":"`` We are judges , not members of Congress . ''","depth":9},{"id":117,"text":"`` Instead of a hard-earned victory","depth":13},{"id":118,"text":"won through the democratic process ,","depth":13},{"id":119,"text":"today ' s victory is brought about by judicial dictate","depth":12},{"id":120,"text":"- judges","depth":13},{"id":121,"text":"latching on to a novel form of living literalism","depth":13},{"id":122,"text":"to rewrite ordinary meaning","depth":13},{"id":123,"text":"and remake American law , ''","depth":13},{"id":124,"text":"he wrote .","depth":10},{"id":125,"text":"`` Under the Constitution and laws of the United States , this court is the wrong body","depth":10},{"id":126,"text":"to change American law in that way . ''","depth":10},{"id":127,"text":"Federal appeals courts have been split on the question since 2017 ,","depth":6},{"id":128,"text":"when the U.S. Court of Appeals for the 7th Circuit became the first","depth":8},{"id":129,"text":"to rule","depth":9},{"id":130,"text":"that gay men and lesbians should be covered by the decades-old federal civil rights law .","depth":9},{"id":131,"text":"The U.S. Court of Appeals for the 2nd Circuit ruled for Zarda in 2018 ,","depth":8},{"id":132,"text":"but the 11th Circuit ,","depth":11},{"id":133,"text":"based in Atlanta ,","depth":11},{"id":134,"text":"ruled against Bostock .","depth":10},{"id":135,"text":"The 6th Circuit ,","depth":11},{"id":136,"text":"based in Cincinnati ,","depth":11},{"id":137,"text":"ruled for Stephens .","depth":10},{"id":138,"text":"Congress has debated the issue for decades","depth":9},{"id":139,"text":"but `` repeatedly declined to pass bills","depth":10},{"id":140,"text":"adding sexual orientation to the list of protected traits '' under the law ,","depth":10},{"id":141,"text":"the Justice Department told the justices .","depth":8},{"id":142,"text":"The Democratic-controlled House passed the Equality Act last year ,","depth":9},{"id":143,"text":"which would go beyond the court 's ruling ,","depth":9},{"id":144,"text":"but the Republican-controlled Senate has not considered it .","depth":8},{"id":145,"text":"While proponents of gay , lesbian and transgender rights hailed the decision ,","depth":8},{"id":146,"text":"it came under withering criticism from some conservatives .","depth":8},{"id":147,"text":"Carrie Severino , president of the Judicial Crisis Network , denounced Gorsuch 's opinion in strikingly personal terms .","depth":8},{"id":148,"text":"\" Justice","depth":13},{"id":149,"text":"( Antonin )","depth":13},{"id":150,"text":"Scalia would be disappointed","depth":12},{"id":151,"text":"that his successor has bungled textualism so badly today , for the sake","depth":12},{"id":152,"text":"of appealing to college campuses and editorial boards , ''","depth":12},{"id":153,"text":"she said .","depth":10},{"id":154,"text":"`` This is an ominous sign for anyone","depth":10},{"id":155,"text":"concerned about the future of representative democracy . \"","depth":10}],"relations":[{"parent":311,"left":0,"right":310,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":310,"left":224,"right":309,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":224,"left":186,"right":223,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":186,"left":163,"right":185,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":163,"left":160,"right":162,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":160,"left":1,"right":159,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":15